perty);\\n        }\\n        test.setFork(fork);\\n    }\\n\\n    /**\\n     * Add a new single testcase.\\n     * @param   test    a new single testcase\\n     * @see JUnitTest\\n     * @since Ant 1.2\\n     */\\n    public void addTest(final JUnitTest test) {\\n        tests.add(test);\\n        preConfigure(test);\\n\\n[1764 more lines in file. Use offset=595 to continue.]\"}],\"isError\":false,\"timestamp\":1778083693330}}\n{\"type\":\"message\",\"id\":\"cdb5429d\",\"parentId\":\"68b5eddd\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-05-06T16:08:20.306Z\",\"message\":{\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"thinking\",\"thinking\":\"**Exploring worktree paths**\\n\\nI'm trying to figure out a test path when the worktree is missing. I might need to edit it to an absolute path if I know where it is. Things have gotten a bit strange with the worktrees—maybe there are multiple ones? I'd like to find the directories without using bash. I could check known locations like `/home/.../forge/local_repositories/forge_worktrees` and see if I can read the directory from there.\",\"thinkingSignature\":\"{\\\"id\\\":\\\"rs_08dd4caa7ba0f2930169fb676f2cbc81978da2aa1136e2e59a\\\",\\\"type\\\":\\\"reasoning\\\",\\\"encrypted_content\\\":\\\"gAAAAABp-2dzDlle-mTp1mVnf6bXVEvYwiSHtCxeENVIjA2gMX0omuWMAy5kssJTz73fm6xS4APZU8gUAOb9cxk-RYlrHxckOAnE4Xlc705WLWDI-18ntFH-b5wWG9HcEfZuKNtPnRFdDs7pCjv9naq8gZUnYHCEVeEvsC-J0l4xCF1EXR_QCdf876hhQirccWQSQwYfoemORIwvfpPeAkLPuPxhfI934x3TVNBQXDuK4Bu1Xx15FxfSGg1EjaQueu9EHb_q6uz0XDJI9Odb14HrQ7lSaU6YoUJKfnkf38slcSdvm_LRdZO3_3pSNVGQ-KaJwfONRfqALG7IyjKRQCaIQr5j8YGKGIOeRbMo_R3uLtDASOfvvRa72XwngIdRw5rJyO3pzIkl6XAo6-LFTrQw-27UBFPyifgzWFq_pRrSppd8wvTo7eXmX4eYtxbp_zTVpQ6JzZlzleWIorAhpjpzhAlKz1pO61maOBR_0kBF0dNhlGA3Lg24XdEuO9seysvtzRWNLdxnV3t3i9BfMeT3VQw4itbteyQTqCqYxPGdcB5uLGP6MX9uMBD_sVCoXz0SSXN93XDvsHbztUSdlP9FzdCAIzQI3iurXi2VnUwDbOZU5UxH8zXDtbWILF6bh_kehSnZ7BkF4-oEiI4M8t4ISUSA_Go5-HuS6hA1_LtfcAvXxfT-usnB076j9Z4e3dvZk7r6dtUVngHE9GvsFCsA-hLayvi5j4YsckZumzuNRySBiDHAV1nEnLjTYtQj